Have you participated in a previous Gitcoin Grants Round? If so, please name the rounds or link the builder profile associated with previous rounds
Provide a brief overview of your tool, library, or framework. What specific problem or inefficiency in the development process does it address?
questions.explanation:
Otterscan is the most affordable way for regular people to run a mainnet block explorer locally. Since everything is local, everything is fast, private, and it runs on consumer grade hardware.

It is built on top of Erigon, currently the only ETH client able to run an archive node on consumer grade hardware (syncs in 1 day, takes ~1.7 TB; regular external SSDs do the work).

Otterscan implements some non-standard JSON-RPC methods to extract additional information (e.g. internal ETH transfers) directly from Erigon DB.

Then, we use this data with other public datasets (4bytes, Sourcify) to provide a 100% local block explorer. It is a SPA and requires only an Erigon archive node, no additional middleware (SQL DBs, indexers) is necessary.

It supports open standards like ENS, and widespread sources of info like Chainlink for getting historical price info directly from the archive, no external sources are needed.

Community members have even made it available into a dappnode package.

questions.query: How does your project reduce development barriers, improve efficiency, or enhance the security of Web3 projects? Please provide specific examples or metrics if available.
questions.explanation:
Otterscan reduces dependencies on third-parties and provides faster access to onchain info, as well as adding a privacy layer to it.

Also, throught Otterscan APIs, users can have access to information regular nodes does not provide.

data.title: GG22 OSS - Developer Tooling and Libraries

questions.query: Have you participated in a previous Gitcoin Grants Round? If so, please name the rounds or link the builder profile associated with previous rounds.
Provide a brief overview of your tool, library, or framework. What specific problem or inefficiency in the development process does it address?
questions.explanation:
Block explorers are a crucial part of the development cycle, be it for inspecting if your deployments succeeded, or what happened when you called some method in your smart contract.

Otterscan is the most affordable way for regular people to run a mainnet block explorer locally. Since everything is local, everything is fast, private, and it runs on consumer grade hardware.

We also support all testnets, so developers can use it as part of their development cycle at all phases:

local dev/testing: use Otterscan + Anvil

testnet: use Otterscan + erigon running some testnet; use our sponsored hosted versions for testnets

mainnet: use Otterscan + erigon running mainnet

Since it is opensource, users don't need to depend on third-party services.

questions.query: How does your project reduce development barriers, improve efficiency, or enhance the security of Web3 projects? Please provide specific examples or metrics if available.
questions.explanation:
Since it is an explorer, it is able to display everything that happened with a transaction is an user friendly way.

More specifically for smart contract development, since it supports all testnets, developers can test their applications and see what happened.

Our trace view is also a great tool for developers to inspect what happened inside the transaction, including all chain of calls.

questions.query: Describe the current usage and support for your tool within the developer community. This could include GitHub stars, downloads, or testimonials from developers.
questions.explanation:
Because Otterscan is meant for users to run locally, we don't have metrics on actual usage.

So we have some indirect success metrics:

Stars on GitHub: https://github.com/otterscan/otterscan/stargazers

Number of pulls on Docker Hub: https://hub.docker.com/r/otterscan/otterscan

questions.query: Outline your project's roadmap and how the grant funds will be used to achieve your development goals.
questions.explanation:
Our main goals right now are:

- Better support upcoming Erigon 3
- Support Pectra upgrade

Funds will be used to ensure long term project continuity and cover team expenses.
